11: Why did it have to be you...
23: It's about time... you were honest...
38: Why can't I go outside? I wanna go!
41:
You mustn't. There are scary
dragons waiting out there.
46:
But I wanna go to Mosnia! They have
a princess, right?
56:
If you're looking for a princess, you
need not look further than yourself.
69:
Barely. That was too close for my
liking.
85:
You should sound a little happier
about the fact!
87:
Being alive means getting hugs and
all those other good things!
95:
There's no more mana left in the
town. I've lost.
102:
Stop being such a dummy. As long
as we're still kicking, we're not done!
104:
We've got our whole lives ahead of
us!
112:
Hey, Simon, did you make a grave
for Grey? I'd like to pay a visit if you
did!
116:
...I suppose, as the loser, I should at
least honor that wish.
122:
And you're coming with. Let's all go
together, guys!
126:
It's hard to believe that he's actually
underneath here, especially since I
can't see him.
130:
...My father was an indecisive man.
He constantly debated what to do
about you.
132:
He continued lying about your
identity, all the while wondering if he
should confess the truth and free
you.
134:
In the end, he passed with the
burden of those lies weighing down
on his shoulders.
138:
That's horrible... If only he had said
something...
141: That was the kind of man he was.
147:
I would've liked to see that side of
him.
150:
What about you? How do you feel

154:
I... I set out to accomplish what he
couldn't, and I failed.
156:
Honestly, I should've just left you and
all this mess behind from the start.
158:
But it bothered me more than it
should've to see you living like a
princess, when your fate should
have been no better than mine...
163:
Hehehe, we're not so different after
all, huh? After you threw such a fit

170: So much effort wasted, and for what?
173:
I wonder what my father would've
had to say about  it.
176:
Hmmm... Simon, you think we're
siblings?
180: Huh? Why would you think that?
183:
Well, Grey's my family, and you're his
family, so that makes us family!
187:
Siblings fight all the time, right? We
just had our first sibling fight!
191:
Pfft, hahaha! The world would be in
shambles if that's how siblings
actually fought.
196: Hey! World's still here, isn't it?
199:
Come on, bring it in! We should hug

203:
...I see there's no arguing this. Very
well.
209:
I guess this is goodbye for now.
You'll come visit though, won't you?
213:
Fret not, for my travels carry me far
and wide. Do treat me to some
more potatoes when I next stop by.
216:
We'll definitely come back to hang
out, so no more fighting in the
meantime, got it?
221:
I'm not sure how to properly convey
this, but... I am extremely sorry for
everything I put you through.
225:
It's all right. Nobody was seriously
hurt, and we ended up finishing the
job we were hired to do.
231: Prika, do you remember our promise?
234:
Yeah! Someday, I'll come visit your
home, and you'll show me around!
237: I shall be more than happy to do so.
242:
What about us, then? What are our
plans from here on out?
246:
Well... You have to watch over me,
don't you?
248:
And I can't just leave you to get
lonely and cause trouble again!
253:
I'm pretty sure you don't need a
keeper anymore, especially not one
you can beat.
257:
Do whatever you want to do, Prika.
Go wherever you want to go. You
are free.
262:
Watch over the place while I'm
gone, Simon!
266:
Hahaha... A sister like her is going to
be a handful.
269:
But we'll be fine from now on. Won't
we, Father?
